define('CHURCH_NEWS_CONTENT','<p><span id="1214416855503E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416846338E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416838649E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416829886E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416804649E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416797164E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416790312E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416782815E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416775350E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416761748E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416750895E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416743269E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416735466E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416728363E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416710703E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416693901E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416686676E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416677943E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416662434E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416654147E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416646695E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416639110E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416621885E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416613240E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416595674E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416588845E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416576247E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416567939E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416560734E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416549825E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416539806E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416519672E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416513139E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416504063E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416495267E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416487558E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span id="1214416461456E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: xx-large;"><strong> </strong>
<p align="center"><span id="1214416431988S" style="display: none"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><em><strong>Services and other activities in area churches this week include the following:</strong></em></span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>ABINGDON EPISCOPAL</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Abingdon Episcopal Church, White Marsh, will hold Sunday service (Rite Two) at 9:30 a.m.&nbsp;with the Rev. Hugh C. White as the guest celebrant.&nbsp; </span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Vacation Bible School continues from 9 a.m.-noon through Friday for ages three through fifth grade. A science supper will be served at 6 p.m.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>ABUNDANT HARVEST WORSHIP CENTER</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">On Sunday, Marvin C. Spencer will speak on "Prepared for War" at the 10:30 a.m. service in Abundant Harvest Worship Center which meets in Ware Academy, 7936 John Clayton Memorial Highway, Gloucester.&nbsp;Equipping the Saints class will start at 9:30.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>APOSTLES LUTHERAN</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Apostles Lutheran Church, Gloucester, will join St. Therese Roman Catholic Church, Gloucester, on Saturday, at St. Therese in a barbecue supper and ecumenical evening prayer service to celebrate our freedom and pray for Christian unity. The supper will begin at 6:15 p.m.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>BELLAMY UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Rappahannock District Youth Choir will perform at both the 8:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday in Bellamy United Methodist Church, Gloucester. Health and Welfare will also collect items for the Laurel Shelter on Sunday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>BETHANY UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Rappahannock District Youth Choir, of which Bethany members Ashley Polk&nbsp;and Timothy Hart are members, will present a concert at Bethany United Methodist Church, Gloucester Point, at 7:30 p.m. Saturday. The 80-voice choir spends one week doing hands-on mission work and practicing their music. The second week they perform concerts in churches throughout the district.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of Pastor Steve Young for both the 8:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday will be "A God in Our Own Image."</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>BETHEL UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of the Rev. Michael Sullivan, pastor of Bethel United Methodist Church, Onemo, at the 8:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday will be "Child Sacrifice."</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>CENTRAL UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of the Rev. Carl Ulrich, pastor of Central United Methodist Church, Mathews, at both the 8:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday will be "A Mountain Called Moriah." The Rappahannock District Youth Choir will perform at 7:30 p.m.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Vacation Bible School, "God&rsquo;s Big Backyard," continues from 6-8:30 p.m. through Friday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>CHURCH OF ABRAHAM</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Minister Desmond Forrest, associate minister of Zion Baptist Church, Cardinal, will preach at the 10:30 a.m. fellowship service Sunday in Church of Abraham, 17 Plaza Shopping Center, Ordinary. There will be no 1 p.m. service.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">On Saturday, there will be a Missions Fundraiser Extravaganza from 7 a.m.-3 p.m. in 17 Plaza Shopping Center. The event will include a yard sale, bake and sandwich sale. All proceeds will benefit the Missions, Kinshasa (Africa).</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>CHURCH OF THE LIVING WORD</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Church of the Living Word, 8144 Tidemill Road, Hayes, continues its summer revival service at 7 p.m. Thursday. Pastor David Spratley of Rising Sun Baptist Church, Lackey, will speak, accompanied by his congregation, ushers and choir.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of Senior Pastor Gregory Woodard, at the 10 a.m. service Sunday will be "Trusting God in Difficult Times." Family and Friends Day, "Reaching Families," will be celebrated at 3 p.m. Pastor Melvin Walton of New Birth Church of Deliverance, Newport News, will be the guest speaker, accompanied by his congregation, choir and ushers.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The book of Esther will be the 7 p.m. Wednesday Bible study topic.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>FAITH BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Pastor Werlie Hendrix of Faith Baptist Church, Bohannon, will&nbsp;preach from 1st Corinthians chapter 14 during the 10:45 a.m. service on Sunday.&nbsp;Bible studies for all ages will be held Sunday evening at 6 o&rsquo;clock.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Bible study "Downpour" will meet on Wednesday evening at the church office.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">It was also announced that&nbsp;the church will have a booth at the Gwynn&rsquo;s Island Festival on Saturday and hand out free Bibles, church brochures and flyers on the upcoming Sail Camp.&nbsp;There will also be church-wide bowling from 6-9 p.m. Saturday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>FIRST ASSEMBLY OF GOD</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">First Assembly of God, Route 33, east of West Point, continues its Vacation Bible School, "God&rsquo;s Big Backyard," from 6:30-8:30 p.m. through Friday, for ages three to 12.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>FIRST BAPTIST, MATHEWS</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Men and Women in Excellence Fellowship program will be held at 3:30 p.m. Sunday in First Baptist Church, Mathews. John Smith and the MGM Tri-County Choir will sing.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>FIRST PRESBYTERIAN</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Pastor Bob Murdock will speak at the 8:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday in First Presbyterian Church, Gloucester.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>GLOUCESTER POINT BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of Pastor Bruce Warrington of Gloucester Point Baptist at the 11 a.m. service Sunday will be "Be Saved and Receive God&rsquo;s Spirit." A study on Ephesians 4 will be held at 6:30 p.m. in the Fellowship Hall.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Activities on&nbsp;Wednesday will include: 9:30 a.m., Seniors&rsquo; Morning Out, 6 p.m., Teens Living for Christ, 6:30, prayer meeting, and 7:30, choir practice.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>GLOUCESTER UNION RELIEF ASSOCIATION OF MISSIONARY BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Gloucester Union Relief Association of Missionary Baptist will hold its regular session on Saturday and Sunday at Zion Hill Baptist Church, Pinero. The executive session will meet at 10 a.m. and each church is asked to send two delegates. The Institute Session will meet at 11 a.m. with the Rev. Fred Carter of Shepherdsville Baptist Church, Ark, as institute instructor.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Sunday session will meet at 9:45 a.m. with church school followed by youth period and worship. The Rev. Stevens Burrell, pastor of Gleaning Baptist Church, Dutton, will preach and the choir of Zion Hill will sing.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>GROVES MEMORIAL PRESBYTERIAN</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">"America for Christ" will be the sermon topic of the Rev. Thomas Bunting, guest preacher, at Groves Memorial Presbyterian Church, 9117 Glass Road, Glass, at the 10 a.m. service on Sunday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>GWYNN&rsquo;S ISLAND BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of the Rev. David Patton, pastor of Gwynn&rsquo;s Island Baptist Church, at both the 8:30 casual and 11 a.m. services Sunday will be "Psalm 100." Joan Foster will provide special music at the early service and the church choir will sing at the 11 o&rsquo;clock service.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>LIGHTHOUSE WORSHIP CENTER</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Lighthouse Worship Center, Ordinary, will be the distribution site for the USDA food distribution at 12 noon Thursday.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Other activities include: Friday, Children&rsquo;s Ministry will have a lock-in for first through fifth grade students; Friday, July 4, church picnic, 10 a.m.-5 p.m., Beaverdam Park, Whitcomb Lodge.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>MACEDONIA BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Pastor Search Committee of Macedonia Baptist Church, Foster, will meet at 6:30 p.m. Thursday.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Rev. Eddie Heath, interim pastor, will preach at the 11 a.m. service Sunday. The SonShine Choir will practice in the Fellowship Hall during the service.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>MATHEWS BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Mathews Baptist Church, Hudgins, will hold a combined worship service at 10:45 a.m. Sunday. The sermon topic will be "Eternal Vigilance, the Price of Freedom," in observance of Independence Day. There will also be a baptism service. Sunday school will be held at 9:30.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">On Wednesday the Rev. Edward Inabinet, pastor, will lead a prayer time and Bible study, "3:16."</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>MATHEWS CHAPEL UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Lay speaker Melvin Callis will speak at the 11 a.m. service Sunday in Mathews Chapel United Methodist Church, Cobbs Creek.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">A trip to the United Methodist Urban Ministries is planned for July 16. Contact Peggy Newsome, 725-3721, for more information.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>MORNING GLORY BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Morning Glory Baptist Church, 8956 Morning Glory Road, Woods Cross Roads, will be the site for the USDA food program from 3-5 p.m. Friday. New applicants are always accepted, a release noted.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>NEWINGTON BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Vacation Bible School continues at Newington Baptist Church, Gloucester, from 6:30-9 p.m. through Friday.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of Pastor Mike Gray at the 10:15 a.m. service Sunday will be "Discovering Jesus&rsquo; Miraculous Power." A covered-dish luncheon and business meeting will follow the service. Small group Bible Study will be held at 6 p.m.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Other activities will include: Saturday, 10:30 a.m.-12 noon, Angel Food Ministry delivery; Tuesday, 7 p.m., Men&rsquo;s Ministry, Boy Scouts, and Women&rsquo;s Bible Study; Wednesday, 5:45 p.m., prayer meetings, 6:30 p.m., AWANA and youth, 7 p.m., Praise Team.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>OLIVE BRANCH UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Olive Branch United Methodist, 10833 Harcum Road, Gloucester, continues Vacation Bible School&nbsp;from 9:30 a.m.-12 noon through Friday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>PETSWORTH BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of Pastor Dennis Hollandsworth of Petsworth Baptist Church, Gloucester, at the 8:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday will be "A Collection of Wise Sayings." Rudy Waters will have the special music. A Summer Sizzling Social with a dessert bar will be held at 6 p.m., followed by praise service at 7 o&rsquo;clock.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Senior Adult Ministry will have a salad bar lunch and fellowship from 10 a.m.-1 p.m. Wednesday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>PROVIDENCE BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Providence Baptist Church, Hayes, will hold an Independence Day celebration at 6 p.m. Saturday, July 5. The celebration will include a boxed fried chicken dinner, music and entertainment by "The Carrolls" and the Sanctuary Choir, and a fireworks display. Dinner tickets will cost $3 for adults, $2 for children and $10 maximum for families, and may be picked up at the church office.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Carrolls will also be in concert at 6 p.m. Sunday, July 6.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>REVIVAL OUTREACH CENTER</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Revival Outreach Center, Maryus Road, Maryus, will have gospel singing at 6 p.m. Saturday.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>SAMUEL&rsquo;S WORD OF FREEDOM FELLOWSHIP OUTREACH</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Samuel&rsquo;s Word of Freedom Fellowship Outreach, 2692 Carmines Island Road, Hayes, will hold a free clothes jamboree, picnic, food, games, and toys, from 9 a.m.-4 p.m. Saturday. A release noted that everyone is encouraged to bring four canned goods to the jamboree for the "Can Goods to Haiti" drive. It was also noted that Wenda Royster, founder of www.praylive.com, will be at the event to ask for commitment/support and to share how prayer is changing lives around the world. A prayer revival will be held on Saturday, Aug. 30, at the Abingdon Ruritan Club, 8784 Guinea Road, Bena. Contact Lady Denson, 642-5132 or 757-593-1601, for more information.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>SEVERN CHURCH</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Adam West, son of Pastor Bill and Barbara West of Severn Church, Naxera, will share his testimony at the 11 a.m. service Sunday. He will talk about how he was involved in a terrible car accident 10 years ago that almost took his life and tell what God has done in his life, a release said.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>SHEPHERDSVILLE BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Rev. Fred Carter, senior pastor of Shepherdsville Baptist Church, 8729 Fary&rsquo;s Mill Road, Ark, will preach at the 8 a.m. service Sunday. The Rev. Richard Jackson will lead the congregational singing.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>ST. MATTHEW UNITED METHODIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of the Rev. Michael Sullivan, pastor of St. Matthew United Methodist Church, Peary, at the 9:45 a.m. service Sunday will be "Child Sacrifice."</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>ST. THERESE ROMAN CATHOLIC</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">An Ecumenical barbecue supper and evening prayer service to celebrate our freedom in honor of Independence Day will be held on Saturday at St. Therese Roman Catholic Church, Gloucester. The supper will begin at 6:15 p.m. followed by the prayer service at 7 o&rsquo;clock. The event is being held jointly with Apostles Lutheran and First Presbyterian churches. The prayer service will be led by the Rev. Doug Nagel, pastor of First Presbyterian, the Rev. Jim Larson, pastor of Apostles, and the Rev. Jim Cowles, pastor of St. Therese. Canned goods and/or free-will offering will benefit the Salvation Army.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>UNION BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of Pastor Patrick Coffey of Union Baptist Church, Achilles, at the 11 a.m. service Sunday will be "Glory to God."&nbsp;His topic at the 7 p.m. service will be "How to be a Healthy Church (Part 9)."</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Other activities will include: Thursday, 7 p.m., community movie night; Tuesday, 6:30 p.m., youth activity (7-12 grades); Wednesday, 7 p.m., game night (1-6 grades), Pastor Coffey will speak on "Be Sure of What You Hear."</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>UNITARIAN UNIVERSALIST FELLOWSHIP OF THE RAPPAHANNOCK</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Bob Duryea, will speak on "Why More is Less" at 10:30 a.m. Sunday in Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of the Rappahannock.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The Fellowship meets at the White Stone Woman&rsquo;s Club building at 560 Chesapeake Drive in White Stone.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>WAY TO ETERNAL LIFE</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Youth Vacation Bible School&nbsp;continues from 6:30-8:30 p.m. through Friday at Way to Eternal Life, 2540 Hayes Road.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Pastor Rev. Leon Abbott will preach&nbsp;at the 11 a.m. service Sunday, preceded by&nbsp;10 o&rsquo;clock Sunday school. Tickets will be available for&nbsp;an upcoming backyard movie night beginning on Sunday.&nbsp;Proceeds will benefit the Hallelujah Carnival Night.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">It was also announced that Wednesday night Bible Study has been suspended until mid-August due to summer vacation time. Contact&nbsp;684-5880 to get a schedule of events.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>WESTVILLE CHRISTIAN</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Westville Christian Church, Mathews, will dedicate its new organ at the 11 a.m. service Sunday. There will be a service of meditation on hymns, and a lunch will follow.</span></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small;">
<p align="center"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p align="center"><strong>WHITE MARSH BAPTIST</strong></p>
</span><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: MyriadPro-Regular;">
<p align="left"><span style="font-family: Verdana;">The sermon topic of the Rev. Scott Pond, pastor of White Marsh Baptist Church, at the 10:30 a.m. service Sunday will be "What Does It Mean to be a Christian?"&nbsp;On Sunday evening at 4 o&rsquo;clock, the congregation will have a fifth Sunday fellowship cookout in the picnic shelter.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;">On Saturday, the youth will hold a yard sale beginning at 8 a.m.&nbsp;A hot dog meal will be served as well to help raise funds.&nbsp;The proceeds from the sale will go to support "Doctors without Borders," a non-profit agency that provides world-wide medical care in poor nations.&nbsp;The church will hold a "Neighborhood Bible Blitz," sharing information about the church and Vacation Bible School along with distributing Bibles throughout the area, from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m.</span></p>
</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span id="1214416432462E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span></p>');
